Steven F. Udvar-Hazy Photographs






Be the first to review this product


A Selection of collector-grade prints of Smithsonian National Air & Space Museum Steven F. Udvar-Hazy Center photographs presented to special guests under the auspices of the grand opening of the Center on December 15, 2003.  The three aircraft selected for this Portfolio include the Lockheed SR-71A; the BAZ/Aerospatiale Concorde; and the Rockwell International Space Shuttle Enterprise.  The 8 inch by 11 inch photos are printed on 16 inch by 22 inch heavy paper sheets and preserved inside a large portfolio folder that measures the same.



