National Air and Space Museum
Washington, DC




National Air and Space Museum




The 1903 Wright Flyer, the Ryan NYP Spirit of St. Louis, and the Apollo 11 Command Module Columbia are just a few of the historic firsts on display at the Museum in Washington, DC. Explore thematic exhibitions on the history of aviation and spaceflight. Take in an IMAX film, planetarium show, or observe the Sun and nearby planets at our Public Observatory. 


Regular Hours: 10:00 am - 5:30 pmOpen daily except December 25See extended hours scheduleAdmission FREE 

Independence Ave at 6th St, SWWashington, DC 20560202-633-2214  


 


 




Steven F. Udvar-Hazy Center
Chantilly, VA




Steven F. Udvar-Hazy Center




Hundreds of aircraft and spacecraft are on display in two massive hangars, including a Lockheed SR-71 Blackbird, the Boeing B-29 Superfortress Enola Gay, and the Space Shuttle Discovery. View aircraft flying in and out of Dulles International Airport from our Observation Tower. Watch restoration specialists restore artifacts in our Restoration Hangar. 


Regular Hours: 10:00 am - 5:30 pmOpen daily except December 25See extended hours scheduleAdmission FREE - Parking $15 

14390 Air and Space Museum PkwyChantilly, Virginia 20151703-572-4118 


 







